### üîπ **Comparison: "Digital Attic" vs. "Focused Workshop"**

The key insight is that **they serve different purposes, and both are valuable.** You need a place to sketch freely (the attic) and a place to build cleanly (the workshop). Our new system formalizes this separation.

```bash
# Create unsorted folder
mkdir -p .specstory/history/unsorted
# Iterate over each file in .specstory/history (non-recursive)
for f in .specstory/history/*; do
  [ -f "$f" ] || continue
  lname=$(echo "$(basename "$f")" | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')
  if [[ $lname == *hibiscus* ]]; then dest="projects/01-hibiscus-studio/_history";
  elif [[ $lname == *retail* ]]; then dest="projects/02-retail/_history";
  elif [[ $lname == *gas* ]]; then dest="projects/03-gas-solutions/_history";
  elif [[ $lname == *fitness* ]]; then dest="projects/04-fitness/_history";
  elif [[ $lname == *personal* ]]; then dest="projects/05-personal-development/_history";
  elif [[ $lname == *crm* || $lname == *operations* ]]; then dest="projects/06-crm-role/_history";
  elif [[ $lname == *delphi* ]]; then dest="projects/07-ad-hoc/delphi/_history";
  elif [[ $lname == *nigerian* || $lname == *budget* ]]; then dest="projects/07-ad-hoc/nigerian-budget-research/_history";
  else dest=".specstory/history/unsorted"; fi;
  mkdir -p "$dest";
  cp "$f" "$dest/";
done
```
